Description: Shoulder sherd of Aeolian Black Polychrome pottery closed vessel, possibly an oinochoe; pale brownish-orange fabric with very little gold mica inclusions; exterior: below junction of neck and shoulder, part of two incised tongues (one with added red, the other black); below, white-red-white-red-white band.
Curator's comments: Fabric from this sherd is almost identical to other Aeolian vessels, in particular, see 1924,1201.11.
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p.256, no.3)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.55)
